Suhadii', II, 129-32, tres elague.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Zayʿa was one of the most popular saints in the Chaldean and Assyrian villages. He was a Palestinian and was a missionary to northern Iraq, along with his disciple Tabor. He lived forty years in a cave of Mount Gara.</note>
